{
    "publish_date": "2013-10-30T19:00:16.000Z", 
    "video_length": "PT8M24S", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "Hey, Vsauce. Michael here.", 
            "dur": "1.88", 
            "start": "0.25"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Every cloud", 
            "dur": "0.919", 
            "start": "2.46"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "has a silver lining.", 
            "dur": "2.3", 
            "start": "3.379"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Except nuclear mushroom clouds,\nwhich have a lining of Strontium-90,", 
            "dur": "5.04", 
            "start": "5.68"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Caesium-137 and other radioactive isotopes.", 
            "dur": "3.859", 
            "start": "10.73"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Upon detonation, atoms are literally gutted", 
            "dur": "3.561", 
            "start": "14.589"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and glutton at temperatures exceeding\nthat of the surface", 
            "dur": "3.69", 
            "start": "18.15"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of our Sun.\nIn the 1950s, Harold Edgerton&#39;s", 
            "dur": "4.029", 
            "start": "21.84"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "rapatronic camera caught nuclear fireballs less than a", 
            "dur": "3.381", 
            "start": "25.869"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "thousandth of a second after detonation.\nUsing a special magnetic shutter,", 
            "dur": "4.95", 
            "start": "29.25"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "each exposure lasted only a billionth\nof a second and captured", 
            "dur": "4.99", 
            "start": "34.2"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "an other-worldly creature,\nits energy vaporising the metal wires", 
            "dur": "5.67", 
            "start": "39.19"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "supporting its tower into stringing legs", 
            "dur": "3.58", 
            "start": "44.86"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of plasma. Watch the target", 
            "dur": "3.22", 
            "start": "48.44"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "on the ground.\nNow, roughly visualized, here is a conventional", 
            "dur": "4.289", 
            "start": "51.66"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "TNT explosion. Now, on the same spot,", 
            "dur": "3.561", 
            "start": "55.949"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "a similarly sized bomb that uses nuclear", 
            "dur": "3.59", 
            "start": "59.51"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "fission.", 
            "dur": "1.2", 
            "start": "63.1"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "When &#39;Little Boy&#39; was detonated over", 
            "dur": "2.94", 
            "start": "74.6"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Hiroshima only 1.38% of its uranium", 
            "dur": "4.29", 
            "start": "77.54"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "actually fissioned.\nThe rest was blown away before", 
            "dur": "3.61", 
            "start": "81.83"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that could happen, which means, as\nEric Schlosser points out, the", 
            "dur": "3.88", 
            "start": "85.44"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "fission of merely 0.7 grams", 
            "dur": "3.06", 
            "start": "89.32"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of uranium, that&#39;s less than the weight of\na banknote, was enough to kill", 
            "dur": "4.92", 
            "start": "92.38"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "80,000 people and destroy two-thirds", 
            "dur": "3.94", 
            "start": "97.3"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of city&#39;s buildings. When a country has\ntens of thousands of nuclear weapons", 
            "dur": "6.56", 
            "start": "101.24"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "ready to go,", 
            "dur": "0.84", 
            "start": "107.8"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "accidents are a possibility.", 
            "dur": "3.41", 
            "start": "108.64"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This was a problem during the Cold War and it still", 
            "dur": "3.75", 
            "start": "112.05"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is a problem. What if there is a fire\nor a miscommunication or a rogue", 
            "dur": "5.23", 
            "start": "115.8"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "officer decides to", 
            "dur": "1.28", 
            "start": "121.03"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "set one off. Or what if someone just drops", 
            "dur": "4.07", 
            "start": "122.31"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "a warhead? How much risk", 
            "dur": "3.23", 
            "start": "126.38"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is too much, I asked Schlosser.", 
            "dur": "3.31", 
            "start": "129.61"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The acceptable probability of a nuclear weapon", 
            "dur": "3.46", 
            "start": "132.92"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "accident? What is it now?", 
            "dur": "2.9", 
            "start": "136.38"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The acceptable probability", 
            "dur": "1.519", 
            "start": "139.28"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of the detonation of a nuclear weapon\nin an accident is one in a million.", 
            "dur": "4.141", 
            "start": "140.799"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In 2012, the odds of your dying", 
            "dur": "3.519", 
            "start": "144.94"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in a commercial airliner accident\nwere about one in forty", 
            "dur": "3.771", 
            "start": "148.459"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "million. So that&#39;s even more remote than\nthe accidental detonation of a nuclear weapon.", 
            "dur": "4.72", 
            "start": "152.23"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "There have been &#39;oopsie daisy&#39; moments\nwith nuclear weapons", 
            "dur": "4.2", 
            "start": "156.95"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "on US soil. Luckily, none that\nresulted in critical mass", 
            "dur": "4.33", 
            "start": "161.15"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but accidents nonetheless.\nJust like when you", 
            "dur": "3.59", 
            "start": "165.48"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "pee your pants, except your pants\nare the entire planet", 
            "dur": "4.58", 
            "start": "169.07"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and the &quot;P&quot; stands for Plutonium.", 
            "dur": "3.52", 
            "start": "173.65"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Eureka comes from ancient", 
            "dur": "2.52", 
            "start": "178.3"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Greek, meaning &quot;I have found it!&quot; And in", 
            "dur": "3.581", 
            "start": "180.829"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Eureka, North Carolina you can find", 
            "dur": "3.079", 
            "start": "184.41"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it. A giant sign that says", 
            "dur": "3.261", 
            "start": "187.489"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Nuclear mishap&quot;. On my birth date", 
            "dur": "3.66", 
            "start": "190.75"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the year my father was born,\na US B-52 bomber carrying", 
            "dur": "4.6", 
            "start": "194.41"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "two 4 megaton thermonuclear bombs", 
            "dur": "3.55", 
            "start": "199.01"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "over North Carolina tumbled", 
            "dur": "3.11", 
            "start": "202.56"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "from the sky. A loose lanyard in the\ncockpit snagged the bomb release", 
            "dur": "5.039", 
            "start": "205.67"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "switch.\nEach bomb contained a greater explosive yield", 
            "dur": "4.701", 
            "start": "210.709"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "than all munitions ever detonated by mankind", 
            "dur": "3.38", 
            "start": "215.41"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "combined.\nLieutenant Jack ReVell discovered that only", 
            "dur": "4.5", 
            "start": "218.79"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "one safety mechanism didn&#39;t fail that day.", 
            "dur": "3.449", 
            "start": "223.29"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "A single low voltage arming switch remained", 
            "dur": "3.511", 
            "start": "226.739"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "untouched during the crash.\nAnd that one switch is why,", 
            "dur": "4.01", 
            "start": "230.25"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "he explained in 2011, we don&#39;t have", 
            "dur": "3.03", 
            "start": "234.28"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "a bay where North Carolina is today.", 
            "dur": "3.42", 
            "start": "237.31"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The bombs were recovered... mostly.", 
            "dur": "3.7", 
            "start": "240.73"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The uranium-rich Secondary\nof one of the bombs was", 
            "dur": "3.8", 
            "start": "244.43"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "never found. To this day it remains buried", 
            "dur": "3.6", 
            "start": "248.23"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "underground in North Carolina.\nHere&#39;s something you can try", 
            "dur": "5.51", 
            "start": "251.83"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "at home.", 
            "dur": "1.99", 
            "start": "257.34"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Build a nuclear reactor.", 
            "dur": "2.4", 
            "start": "259.33"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In 1994, a 17-year-old David Han attempted to build", 
            "dur": "5.32", 
            "start": "262.14"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "a nuclear reactor in his mother&#39;s backyard", 
            "dur": "3.23", 
            "start": "267.47"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in Michigan. It wasn&#39;t that difficult. For instance,", 
            "dur": "3.42", 
            "start": "270.7"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "common everyday smoke detectors\ncontain small amounts of", 
            "dur": "3.96", 
            "start": "274.12"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "radioactive Americium.\nAnd old glow in the dark paint", 
            "dur": "3.92", 
            "start": "278.08"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "contains Radium. His reactor never\nreached critical mass but it did succeed", 
            "dur": "5.14", 
            "start": "282"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in exposing his neighborhood", 
            "dur": "1.87", 
            "start": "287.14"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to 1000 times the regular dosage", 
            "dur": "3.49", 
            "start": "289.01"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of background radiation. It was declared a\nSuperfund hazardous materials cleanup", 
            "dur": "5.26", 
            "start": "292.5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "site", 
            "dur": "0.52", 
            "start": "297.76"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and all of his work was confiscated by\nauthorities and buried", 
            "dur": "3.71", 
            "start": "298.28"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in Utah. It didn&#39;t end", 
            "dur": "3.13", 
            "start": "301.99"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "there. In 2007 David Hahn was", 
            "dur": "3.8", 
            "start": "305.12"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "arrested for stealing smoke detectors\nfrom an apartment building.", 
            "dur": "4.31", 
            "start": "308.92"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "His face was covered with sores believed\nto be caused by constant exposure to", 
            "dur": "5.78", 
            "start": "313.23"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "radioactive materials.", 
            "dur": "1.8", 
            "start": "319.01"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Three days after Little Boy was dropped\non Hiroshima by the Enola Gay", 
            "dur": "5.27", 
            "start": "320.81"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Charles Sweeney was ordered to drop Fatman", 
            "dur": "3.56", 
            "start": "326.08"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "on Kokura. He flew boxcar over the city for nearly an", 
            "dur": "3.75", 
            "start": "329.64"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "hour with the bomb bay doors open,\nbut it was cloudy.", 
            "dur": "3.52", 
            "start": "333.39"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Sweeney couldn&#39;t achieve visual\nconfirmation of the target and was", 
            "dur": "3.83", 
            "start": "336.91"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "forced", 
            "dur": "0.8", 
            "start": "340.74"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to go to the secondary target - Nagasaki,", 
            "dur": "3.22", 
            "start": "341.54"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "where 75,000 people died instead.", 
            "dur": "4.21", 
            "start": "344.76"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Kokura was spared because of the clouds.", 
            "dur": "3.26", 
            "start": "348.97"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We can build a weapon", 
            "dur": "3.12", 
            "start": "352.23"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that mimics the furnace of our Sun\nand the winds of Neptune but yet we can&#39;t", 
            "dur": "5.8", 
            "start": "355.35"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "predict the weather more than\na few minutes ahead of time.", 
            "dur": "5.56", 
            "start": "361.15"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "During World War 2\nJapanese soldiers spot for their", 
            "dur": "3.65", 
            "start": "366.71"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "emperor in ways that made allied troops speechless.", 
            "dur": "4.13", 
            "start": "370.36"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Kamikaze planes and torpedoes,\ndriven by a single pilot,", 
            "dur": "4.19", 
            "start": "374.49"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "lost after use. When outnumbered,", 
            "dur": "3.63", 
            "start": "378.68"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "without hope, Japanese soldiers were\nreported to have thrown themselves", 
            "dur": "4.13", 
            "start": "382.31"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "off clips or swam out to sea to drown", 
            "dur": "4.08", 
            "start": "386.44"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "rather than surrendered. Even after two", 
            "dur": "3.239", 
            "start": "390.52"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "atomic bomb attacks,\nthe Japanese Minister of War", 
            "dur": "3.171", 
            "start": "393.759"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "urged his people to continue fighting.", 
            "dur": "3.12", 
            "start": "396.93"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But on August 14th, 1945, the Emperor of Japan", 
            "dur": "4.51", 
            "start": "400.05"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "overruled that decision and unconditionally", 
            "dur": "3.4", 
            "start": "404.56"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "surrendered. Men had leapt of off cliffs", 
            "dur": "3.91", 
            "start": "407.96"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "for him, but in his own words, \nthe enemy has for the first time", 
            "dur": "4.609", 
            "start": "411.87"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "used cruel bombs.", 
            "dur": "3.03", 
            "start": "416.479"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The heavy casualties are beyond measure.", 
            "dur": "3.271", 
            "start": "419.509"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Richard Feynman received\nthe Nobel Prize in Physics", 
            "dur": "4.319", 
            "start": "422.78"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in 1965. He also helped develop\nthe first atomic bomb", 
            "dur": "4.871", 
            "start": "427.099"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "at Los Alamos.\nIn &quot;The Meaning of It All,&quot; he wrote", 
            "dur": "4.1", 
            "start": "431.97"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Is science of any value?&quot;", 
            "dur": "3.069", 
            "start": "436.07"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And below that,\n&quot;I think a power to do something", 
            "dur": "4.261", 
            "start": "439.139"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is of value.&quot; He elaborates by talking", 
            "dur": "3.579", 
            "start": "443.4"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "about keys. Everything we learned about\nthe universe, everything we invent or", 
            "dur": "5.171", 
            "start": "446.979"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "discover within it,", 
            "dur": "1.41", 
            "start": "452.15"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is a key to the gates of heaven.", 
            "dur": "3.889", 
            "start": "453.56"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But the same key will", 
            "dur": "3.301", 
            "start": "457.449"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "also open the gates to hell.", 
            "dur": "3.259", 
            "start": "460.75"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The Titan II Missile is great for delivering", 
            "dur": "3.051", 
            "start": "464.009"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "lethal nuclear warheads.", 
            "dur": "2.68", 
            "start": "467.06"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But it also sent Gemini astronauts to space,", 
            "dur": "3.23", 
            "start": "469.74"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "preparing us for a mission to the Moon.", 
            "dur": "3.259", 
            "start": "472.97"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Science doesn&#39;t tell us how to use", 
            "dur": "3.301", 
            "start": "476.229"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "keys. It finds them or predicts them.", 
            "dur": "3.359", 
            "start": "479.53"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "How we use keys is up to us.", 
            "dur": "4.841", 
            "start": "482.889"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And as always,", 
            "dur": "1.19", 
            "start": "487.73"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "thanks for watching.", 
            "dur": "0.94", 
            "start": "488.92"
        }
    ], 
